    <h2>1. INTRODUCTION AND ACCEPTANCE</h2>
    <p><strong>1.1</strong> These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the FutureProof Financial platform ("Platform") and the Equity Preservation Mortgage ("EPM") products and services offered through it.</p>
    <p><strong>1.2</strong> The Platform is operated by FutureProof Financial Pty Ltd, ACN [TBD], holder of <%= details[:licensing_act] %> ("FutureProof", "we", "us", "our").</p>
    <p><strong>1.3</strong> By accessing the Platform, creating an account, submitting an application, or using any of our services, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms and our Privacy Policy.</p>
    <p><strong>1.4</strong> If you do not agree to these Terms, you must not access or use the Platform or our services.</p>
    <p><strong>1.5</strong> These Terms constitute a binding agreement between you and FutureProof Financial Pty Ltd. Where you are applying jointly, references to "you" include each applicant jointly and severally.</p>

    <h2>2. DEFINITIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>2.1</strong> In these Terms, unless the context otherwise requires:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>"AFCA"</strong> means the Australian Financial Complaints Authority;</li>
      <li><strong>"AML/CTF Act"</strong> means the <%= details[:aml_act] %>;</li>
      <li><strong>"ASIC"</strong> means the <%= details[:regulator] %>;</li>
      <li><strong>"Borrower"</strong> means a person who has entered into an EPM contract through the Platform;</li>
      <li><strong>"Comparison Rate"</strong> means the rate calculated in accordance with the National Credit Code to help you identify the true cost of a loan;</li>
      <li><strong>"EPM"</strong> or <strong>"Equity Preservation Mortgage"</strong> means a mortgage product where loan proceeds are invested to generate income for the Borrower while preserving the Borrower's equity in the secured property;</li>
      <li><strong>"Hedging Collar"</strong> means the protective options strategy applied to the Investment Portfolio to limit downside risk while allowing participation in market gains;</li>
      <li><strong>"Holiday Period"</strong> means a period during which the Borrower may elect to suspend Monthly Income payments, with investment returns being reinvested into the Investment Portfolio;</li>
      <li><strong>"Investment Account"</strong> means the custodial account holding the Investment Portfolio established in connection with an EPM;</li>
      <li><strong>"Investment Portfolio"</strong> means the portfolio of investments (primarily international index-linked ETFs and fixed income instruments) managed by the appointed Investment Manager;</li>
      <li><strong>"LTV Ratio"</strong> or <strong>"Loan-to-Value Ratio"</strong> means the ratio of the Loan Amount to the independently assessed market value of the Property;</li>
      <li><strong>"Monthly Income"</strong> means the regular monthly payment made to the Borrower from investment returns;</li>
      <li><strong>"National Credit Code"</strong> means the National Credit Code set out in Schedule 1 to the National Consumer Credit Protection Act 2009 (Cth);</li>
      <li><strong>"NCCP Act"</strong> means the National Consumer Credit Protection Act 2009 (Cth);</li>
      <li><strong>"NNEG"</strong> or <strong>"No Negative Equity Guarantee"</strong> means the protection ensuring the Borrower's mortgage debt does not exceed the property value at settlement;</li>
      <li><strong>"Platform"</strong> means the FutureProof Financial website, applications, and related technology services;</li>
      <li><strong>"Profit Share"</strong> means the distribution of surplus investment returns to the Borrower, assessed every five (5) years;</li>
      <li><strong>"Property"</strong> means the residential real property offered as security for the EPM;</li>
      <li><strong>"Responsible Lending"</strong> means the obligations imposed on credit licensees under Part 3-1 of the NCCP Act to ensure credit contracts are not unsuitable for consumers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. SERVICE DESCRIPTION</h2>
    <p><strong>3.1</strong> FutureProof provides a technology platform that facilitates access to Equity Preservation Mortgage products. Our services include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) EPM product information, quotation, and application processing;</li>
      <li>(b) Property valuation coordination;</li>
      <li>(c) Credit assessment and responsible lending evaluation;</li>
      <li>(d) Investment portfolio establishment and ongoing management;</li>
      <li>(e) Monthly Income distribution;</li>
      <li>(f) Ongoing loan servicing, reporting, and account management;</li>
      <li>(g) Customer support and financial literacy resources.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>3.2</strong> We act as a platform connecting Borrowers with approved lenders and investment managers. We are not the lender of record for any EPM contract unless expressly stated.</p>
    <p><strong>3.3</strong> All quotes, projections, and estimates provided through the Platform are indicative only and are subject to formal valuation, credit assessment, and lender approval.</p>

    <h2>4. REGULATORY STATUS</h2>
    <p><strong>4.1</strong> FutureProof Financial Pty Ltd holds an <%= details[:licensing_act] %>, authorising us to provide financial services in relation to EPM products.</p>
    <p><strong>4.2</strong> We are regulated by the <%= details[:regulator] %> and are subject to the requirements of the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth), the <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>, and all applicable ASIC Regulatory Guides.</p>
    <p><strong>4.3</strong> We hold an Australian Credit Licence authorising us to engage in credit activities as defined under the NCCP Act.</p>
    <p><strong>4.4</strong> We are a member of the <%= details[:dispute_resolution] %>, providing external dispute resolution services to our clients.</p>
    <p><strong>4.5</strong> We comply with our obligations under the <%= details[:aml_act] %>, including customer identification, verification, and ongoing monitoring requirements.</p>

    <h2>5. ELIGIBILITY</h2>
    <p><strong>5.1</strong> To be eligible for an EPM through the Platform, you must:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Be at least 55 years of age at the date of application (or such other minimum age as we may approve on a case-by-case basis with appropriate suitability assessment);</li>
      <li>(b) Be an Australian citizen or permanent resident;</li>
      <li>(c) Own residential real property in Australia with a minimum market value of A$500,000;</li>
      <li>(d) Have legal capacity to enter into a mortgage contract;</li>
      <li>(e) Not be an undischarged bankrupt or subject to any form of insolvency administration;</li>
      <li>(f) Satisfy our responsible lending assessment (see Section 8);</li>
      <li>(g) Satisfy our identity verification and AML/CTF requirements.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>5.2</strong> Meeting the above criteria does not guarantee approval. All applications are subject to a comprehensive assessment including property valuation, credit assessment, and lender approval.</p>
    <p><strong>5.3</strong> We reserve the right to decline any application at our sole discretion, including where the EPM would not be suitable for you based on our responsible lending assessment.</p>

    <h2>6. ACCOUNT REGISTRATION</h2>
