    <h2>7. EPM PRODUCT TERMS</h2>
    <p><strong>7.1 Loan-to-Value Ratio:</strong> The maximum LTV Ratio for any EPM is 80% of the independently assessed market value of the Property. The actual LTV approved will depend on your individual circumstances, property type, and our risk assessment.</p>
    <p><strong>7.2 Loan Terms:</strong> EPMs are available for terms of 10, 15, 20, 25, or 30 years. The appropriate term will be determined based on your age, objectives, and our suitability assessment.</p>
    <p><strong>7.3 Investment Structure:</strong> EPM loan proceeds are invested in a diversified portfolio comprising:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Approximately 70% in international index-linked ETFs (primarily S&amp;P 500 and equivalent broad market index funds);</li>
      <li>(b) Approximately 30% in fixed income and defensive instruments;</li>
      <li>(c) A hedging collar strategy to provide downside protection on the equity component.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>7.4 Monthly Income:</strong> Borrowers receive Monthly Income payments estimated at approximately 1.5% per annum of the property value, paid monthly in arrears. The actual income amount may vary based on investment performance and market conditions.</p>
    <p><strong>7.5 Payments Waterfall:</strong> Investment returns from the Portfolio are applied in the following priority:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) First, to pay all mortgage interest due to the Lender;</li>
      <li>(b) Second, to pay the hedging collar premium;</li>
      <li>(c) Third, to pay the platform and management fees;</li>
      <li>(d) Fourth, to pay the Monthly Income to the Borrower;</li>
      <li>(e) Fifth, any surplus to be reinvested in the Investment Portfolio.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>7.6 Profit Share:</strong> Every five (5) years from the EPM commencement date, surplus investment returns (after all obligations in the payments waterfall have been satisfied) will be assessed and distributed to the Borrower as a Profit Share payment.</p>
    <p><strong>7.7 Equity Preservation:</strong> The EPM is structured so that the Loan Amount remains static (no compounding interest on principal). Upon sale or settlement, the Borrower (or their estate) receives the property proceeds less only the original Loan Amount and any outstanding fees.</p>

    <h2>8. RESPONSIBLE LENDING OBLIGATIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>8.1</strong> We take our responsible lending obligations under Part 3-1 of the NCCP Act seriously. Before entering into any EPM contract, we will:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Make reasonable inquiries about your financial situation, requirements, and objectives;</li>
      <li>(b) Take reasonable steps to verify your financial information;</li>
      <li>(c) Conduct a preliminary assessment that the EPM is not unsuitable for you;</li>
      <li>(d) Provide you with a copy of the assessment on request.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>8.2</strong> Our assessment will consider, among other factors:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Your current income, assets, and liabilities;</li>
      <li>(b) Your ongoing living expenses and financial commitments;</li>
      <li>(c) The impact of the EPM on your Centrelink Age Pension entitlements (if applicable);</li>
      <li>(d) Your age and health circumstances;</li>
      <li>(e) Your stated financial objectives and requirements;</li>
      <li>(f) Whether the EPM product features are suitable for your circumstances.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>8.3</strong> We may decline your application if, in our assessment, the EPM would be unsuitable for you, even if you meet the eligibility criteria in Section 5.</p>
    <p><strong>8.4</strong> You are entitled to request a written copy of our preliminary assessment at any time during the first two (2) years of your EPM. We will provide this within seven (7) business days of your request.</p>

    <h2>9. FEES AND CHARGES</h2>
    <p><strong>9.1</strong> The following fees and charges apply to EPM products (all amounts in Australian Dollars):</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI):</strong> 1.6% of the Loan Amount, payable at settlement and added to the loan balance;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>Platform Fee:</strong> 0.25% per annum of the Investment Portfolio value, deducted monthly from investment returns;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>Hedging Collar Premium:</strong> 0.25% per annum of the equity component of the Investment Portfolio, deducted from investment returns;</li>
      <li>(d) <strong>Application Fee:</strong> A$[Amount], payable upon submission of a formal application;</li>
      <li>(e) <strong>Valuation Fee:</strong> A$[Amount], payable upon engagement of the independent valuer;</li>
      <li>(f) <strong>Legal and Settlement Fees:</strong> A$[Amount], payable at settlement;</li>
      <li>(g) <strong>Annual Account Fee:</strong> A$[Amount] per annum (if applicable).</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>9.2</strong> All fees will be fully disclosed in your credit proposal disclosure document and loan contract before you enter into any binding commitment.</p>
    <p><strong>9.3</strong> The Comparison Rate for your EPM will be calculated and disclosed in accordance with the National Credit Code.</p>
    <p><strong>9.4</strong> We will not charge any fee that has not been disclosed to you in advance, and you will be given the opportunity to review all fees before committing to the EPM.</p>
    <p><strong>9.5</strong> Fees may be varied from time to time with at least 30 days' written notice. Any fee increase during an existing EPM term will be subject to the terms of your loan contract.</p>

    <h2>10. INVESTMENT RISKS AND DISCLAIMERS</h2>
    <p><strong>10.1</strong> The EPM involves investment in financial markets. You acknowledge and accept the following risks:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>Market Risk:</strong> The value of the Investment Portfolio may fluctuate due to changes in equity markets, interest rates, and economic conditions;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>Income Variability:</strong> Monthly Income payments are derived from investment returns and may vary. In periods of sustained poor market performance, income may be reduced or temporarily suspended;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>Currency Risk:</strong> The Investment Portfolio includes international investments denominated in foreign currencies, exposing you to exchange rate fluctuations;</li>
      <li>(d) <strong>Hedging Risk:</strong> The hedging collar provides protection against significant market declines but limits participation in strong market gains;</li>
      <li>(e) <strong>Counterparty Risk:</strong> The risk that a counterparty to an investment transaction may default on its obligations;</li>
      <li>(f) <strong>Regulatory Risk:</strong> Changes in laws, regulations, or tax treatment may affect the EPM product or its returns.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>10.2</strong> Past performance is not a reliable indicator of future performance. All projections, estimates, and illustrations provided through the Platform are based on historical data and financial modelling and should not be relied upon as guarantees of future returns.</p>
    <p><strong>10.3</strong> The information provided on the Platform does not constitute personal financial advice. You should consider obtaining independent financial, legal, and tax advice before entering into an EPM.</p>
    <p><strong>10.4</strong> We do not guarantee any specific investment return, Monthly Income amount, or investment outcome.</p>

    <h2>11. HOLIDAY MECHANISM</h2>
    <p><strong>11.1</strong> The EPM includes a Holiday Period feature allowing you to temporarily suspend Monthly Income payments under certain conditions.</p>
    <p><strong>11.2</strong> During a Holiday Period:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Monthly Income payments to you will cease;</li>
      <li>(b) Investment returns that would otherwise be paid to you will be reinvested in the Investment Portfolio;</li>
      <li>(c) All mortgage interest and fee obligations continue to be met from investment returns;</li>
      <li>(d) The Holiday Period builds a buffer in the Investment Portfolio that may enhance future income or provide additional protection.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>11.3</strong> You may request a Holiday Period by written notice to FutureProof. The maximum duration and frequency of Holiday Periods will be set out in your loan contract.</p>
    <p><strong>11.4</strong> A Holiday Period may also be triggered automatically if the Investment Portfolio falls below certain thresholds, as specified in your loan contract.</p>

    <h2>12. INSURANCE AND NNEG PROTECTION</h2>
    <p><strong>12.1 Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI):</strong> An LMI premium of 1.6% of the Loan Amount is paid at settlement. This insurance protects the lender (not you) in the event of default.</p>
    <p><strong>12.2 No Negative Equity Guarantee (NNEG):</strong> Your EPM includes NNEG protection, which ensures that:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Your total mortgage debt (principal plus accrued interest) will never exceed the market value of the Property at the time of settlement;</li>
      <li>(b) If, upon sale or settlement, the Property value is less than the outstanding debt, the NNEG mechanism absorbs the shortfall;</li>
      <li>(c) Neither you nor your estate will be pursued for any deficit between the debt and the property value;</li>
      <li>(d) NNEG protection is maintained through a combination of pool coverage insurance and reserve mechanisms.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>12.3 Pool Coverage:</strong> FutureProof maintains a pool coverage mechanism that provides additional protection for income continuity and interest servicing during periods of adverse market conditions.</p>
    <p><strong>12.4</strong> You acknowledge that NNEG protection applies at the point of settlement only and does not prevent the nominal debt from temporarily exceeding the property value during the EPM term.</p>

    <h2>13. PROPERTY OBLIGATIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>13.1</strong> As a condition of your EPM, you must:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Maintain comprehensive building insurance over the Property for its full replacement value, with the lender noted as an interested party;</li>
      <li>(b) Pay all council rates, water rates, land tax, and other statutory charges when due;</li>
      <li>(c) Pay all strata levies, body corporate fees, and special levies (if the Property is a strata or community title property) when due;</li>
      <li>(d) Maintain the Property in good repair and condition (fair wear and tear excepted);</li>
      <li>(e) Not make any structural alterations to the Property without the lender's prior written consent;</li>
      <li>(f) Not create any additional mortgage, charge, or encumbrance over the Property without the lender's prior written consent;</li>
      <li>(g) Allow the lender or its agent to inspect the Property upon reasonable notice;</li>
      <li>(h) Notify FutureProof immediately of any material change in circumstances, including change of occupancy, damage to the Property, resumption proceedings, or any event that may affect the Property's value;</li>
      <li>(i) Provide proof of current insurance upon request and annually.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>13.2</strong> Failure to comply with these obligations may constitute an event of default under your loan contract.</p>

    <h2>14. CONSUMER PROTECTIONS UNDER NATIONAL CREDIT CODE</h2>
    <p><strong>14.1</strong> As a regulated credit product, your EPM is subject to the consumer protections in the <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) The right to receive a pre-contractual statement setting out all material terms, fees, and charges;</li>
      <li>(b) The right to receive a credit proposal disclosure document;</li>
      <li>(c) The right to receive periodic statements of your loan account;</li>
      <li>(d) Protection against unjust transactions (sections 76-77 of the National Credit Code);</li>
      <li>(e) The right to apply for a hardship variation if you experience financial difficulty;</li>
      <li>(f) The right to apply to a court to reopen an unjust transaction;</li>
      <li>(g) The right to receive a copy of your loan contract and related documents.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>14.2</strong> If you experience financial difficulty (for example, changes in health, loss of other income, or unexpected expenses), you may apply for a hardship variation under section 72 of the National Credit Code. We will respond to any hardship application within 21 days.</p>
    <p><strong>14.3</strong> You have the right to pay out your EPM in full at any time, subject to any early repayment fees disclosed in your loan contract.</p>

    <h2>15. COOLING-OFF PERIOD</h2>
    <p><strong>15.1</strong> You have a cooling-off period of <%= details[:cooling_off] %> from the date you receive your signed loan contract, during which you may cancel the EPM without penalty.</p>
    <p><strong>15.2</strong> To exercise your cooling-off right, you must provide written notice to FutureProof before the cooling-off period expires. Notice may be sent to legal@futureprooffinancial.co or by post to our registered office.</p>
    <p><strong>15.3</strong> If you cancel during the cooling-off period:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Any funds advanced will be returned to the lender;</li>
      <li>(b) You will not be charged any establishment or exit fees;</li>
      <li>(c) You may be liable for reasonable costs incurred (such as valuation fees and government charges) as permitted by the National Credit Code;</li>
      <li>(d) Any registered mortgage will be discharged at our cost.</li>
    </ul>

